The United States strongly condemns Russia's missile strikes in Ukraine, particularly in Kyiv, which resulted in civilian casualties, destruction of non-military targets, and further demonstrate the brutality of Putin's illegal war on the Ukrainian people. The US expresses condolences to the families of those killed and wishes a speedy recovery to the wounded. The attacks reaffirm the commitment of the US to stand with Ukraine, along with allies and partners, and impose costs on Russia for its aggression. The US also vows to hold Putin and Russia accountable for their war crimes and provide support to Ukrainian forces. The US calls on Russia to immediately end the unprovoked aggression and withdraw its troops from Ukraine.